			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Note: Horse and Drogmor are virtually interchangable.
<br />

<br />
<span style="text-decoration: underline">Where can I buy a Horse?</span>
<br />
Horses are sold in the stable, found in the Bazaar.
<br />

<br />
<span style="text-decoration: underline">Where can I buy a Drogmor?</span>
<br />
Drogmors are sold off a vendor in the Gulf of Gunthak.
<br />

<br />
<span style="text-decoration: underline">How do I ride one?</span>
<br />
Right click the Bridle or Drum in inventory. It will cast a 3 second spell. After three seconds you will be mounted.
<br />

<br />
<span style="text-decoration: underline">How fast are they?</span>
<br />
Horse speed are categorized by their price, and the type of bridle.
<br />

<br />
For horses:
<br />
Rope: Approximately run1 speed.
<br />
Leather: Approximately Jboot speed
<br />
Silk: Approximately SoW speed.
<br />
Chain: Approximately Spirit of Cheetah speed.
<br />
Ornate Chain: Approximately Selo's (bard) speed.
<br />

<br />
<span style="text-decoration: underline">Are their MOB droppable horses?</span>
<br />
Yes.
<br />
Emperor Ssraeshza drops a White Ornate Chain Bridle.
<br />
Lord Inquisitor Seru drops a Black Ornate Chain Bridle
<br />
Additionally, several mobs in Ssraeshza Temple have been known to drop Silk Bridles.
<br />

<br />
<span style="text-decoration: underline">Are their MOB droppable Drogmor drums?</span>
<br />
None have been found yet.
<br />

<br />
<span style="text-decoration: underline">Does color affect speed?</span>
<br />
No. Color has absolutely no affect on speed.
<br />

<br />
<span style="text-decoration: underline">How much do they cost?</span>
<br />
Horses are divided into two categories: White/Black, and Brown/Tan. Brown/Tan horses are cheaper than White/Black horses by about 10%.
<br />
Rope: 8400pp for Tan/Brown, 9450pp for White/Black
<br />
Leather: 27,300pp for Tan/Brown, 31,500pp for White/Black
<br />
Silk: 60,900pp for Tan/Brown, 65,100pp for White/Black
<br />
Chain: 95,550pp for Tan/Brown, 103,950pp for White/Black
<br />

<br />
Drogmors cost as much as White/Black horses.
<br />

<br />
<span style="text-decoration: underline">How can I get horses for cheaper?</span>
<br />
The best way is to increase your CHA stat. At approximately 130CHA, the horse and drogmor vendors will sell at their cheapest price.
<br />

<br />
<span style="text-decoration: underline">Where can I ride a horse?</span>
<br />
Horses can only be ridden in outdoor zones. They cannot be used indoors.
<br />

<br />
<span style="text-decoration: underline">Do any run speed effects change horse speed?</span>
<br />
No. Horses will always overwrite any run speed effects, such as Spirit of Wolf. However, levitate affects from spells such as Spirit of Eagle will take hold.
<br />

<br />
<span style="text-decoration: underline">When I click my bridle. it says I can't ride with the current models. Why?</span>
<br />
Horses can only be ridden if your character's Luclin models are turned on in options. Additionally, Horse and Elemental models must be turned on.
<br />

<br />
<span style="text-decoration: underline">How do I get off my horse?</span>
<br />
Either click the buff in your buff window, or type /dismount (/dism)
<br />

<br />
<span style="text-decoration: underline">How can I hide this annoying horse head?</span>
<br />
The most effective way is to shrink.
<br />

<br />
<span style="text-decoration: underline">What is the difference between a Horse and a Drogmor?</span>
<br />
The main difference is that a Drogmor's head does not block your view, while a Horse's head does.
<br />

<br />
<span style="text-decoration: underline">Is a horse considered a buff?</span>
<br />
Not in the traditional sense. Horses do take up a buff slot, but they cannot be dispelled like normal buffs. In affect, they are a permanent buff.
<br />

<br />
<span style="text-decoration: underline">How do I meditate on a horse?</span>
<br />
As long as you are not moving or attacking, you are meditating.
<br />

<br />
<span style="text-decoration: underline">What about if i cast a spell?</span>
<br />
Even while you are casting spells, you are meditating.
<br />

<br />
<span style="text-decoration: underline">How do I interrupt my spell?</span>
<br />
Move so that you cannot channel your spell. Additionally, you can dismount your horse and interrupt by ducking.<br />_________________<br /><img src=http://members.cox.net/jmattcrews/wizardbook.jpg align=left>[65 Arch Convoker] <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=204546" target="_blank" class="postlink">Sage Xalmat Lunaire</a> (Human) <<a href="http://www.enshadowed.net/" target="_blank" class="postlink">Enshadowed</a>>
<br />
[65 Archon] <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=816142" target="_blank" class="postlink">Eiyana Lunaire</a> (Gnome) <Enshadowed>
<br />
<a href="http://forum.magecompendium.com/tower/viewforum.php?f=9" target="_blank" class="postlink">Lead Librarian</a> of <a href="http://forum.magecompendium.com" target="_blank" class="postlink">The Magician's Tower</a>
